      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 1872: The recovery scheduling reads `ctx-\u003etoReclone` immediately after the load loop, but entries are inserted from the per-conversation async load callbacks. If those callbacks are still running, corrupted repositories can be missed and never re-cloned. Move the re-clone dispatch into the same completion path that runs after `PendingConvCounter` observes all conversations loaded, or otherwise ensure all loaders have completed before moving `toReclone`.\n```suggestion\n// In the all-conversations-loaded completion path, after pending loaders finish:\nif (!ctx-\u003etoReclone.empty()) {\n    dht::ThreadPool::io().run([w \u003d pimpl_-\u003eweak(), toReclone \u003d std::move(ctx-\u003etoReclone)]() {\n        // existing recovery loop\n    });\n}\n```",
