      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 3919: `validate()` stores `git_oid_tostr_s(...)` directly in `std::string` keys. `git_oid_tostr_s` returns a libgit2 thread-local/static buffer, so this is only safe because `emplace` copies immediately; it is easy to misuse and obscures intent. Prefer formatting into a fixed buffer helper and reuse it for all OID keys.\n```suggestion\nauto oidToString \u003d [](const git_oid* oid) {\n    std::array\u003cchar, GIT_OID_HEXSZ + 1\u003e buf {};\n    git_oid_tostr(buf.data(), buf.size(), oid);\n    return std::string {buf.data()};\n};\n```",
